      "span_text": "The 2003 CAP survey of 5624 clinical laboratories, using a fresh-frozen serum reference material with an assigned value of 79.38 mol/L (0.902 mg/dL) by IDMS, showed a range of method-dependent bias across laboratories from an underestimate of 5.28 mol/L (0.06 mg/ dL) to an overestimate of 27.28 mol/L (0.31 mg/dL)  .",
